'''Ahmed Mortadha Ouanes''' ({{langx|ar|مرتضى بن وناس}}; born 2 July 1994) is a Tunisian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa]] and the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

==Club career==
Mortadha is trained at the [[Étoile Sportive du Sahel|Etoile Sportive du Sahel]] (ESS), where he goes through all categories of young people. He started in the first division during the [[2013–14 Tunisian Ligue Professionnelle 1|2013–14 season]].{{citation needed|date=April 2025}}

In January 2015, he was loaned for six months to the [[US Monastir (football)|Monastiran Sports Union]]. His loan with this team turned out to be a failure, since he only played one match in the league.

In July 2015, he transferred to the [[CA Bizertin|Bizertin Athletic Club]] (CAB) With this team, he scored four league goals during the [[2015–16 Tunisian Ligue Professionnelle 1|2015–16 season]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=[EN] : Ben Ouanes récompensé|url=https://www.tunisie-foot.com/2019/10/03/en-ben-ouanes-recompense/|access-date=8 February 2021|website=Tunisie-Foot|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=[Journal des transferts] Mortadha Ben Ouanes au CAB pour 3 saisons|url=https://www.tunisie-foot.com/2015/07/30/journal-des-transferts-mortadha-ben-ouanes-au-cab-pour-3-saisons/|access-date=8 February 2021|website=Tunisie-Foot|language=fr-FR}}</ref>

In January 2018, he found his training club.<ref>{{Cite web|date=16 January 2018|title=Etoile du Sahel : Mortadha Ben Ouanes arrive, Ndoye s'éloigne !|url=http://kapitalis.com/tunisie/2018/01/16/etoile-sahel-mortadha-ben-ouanes-arrive-ndoye-seloigne/|access-date=8 February 2021|website=Kapitalis|language=fr-FR}}</ref>

During the [[2019–20 Tunisian Ligue Professionnelle 1|2019–20 season]], he scored four league goals with [[Étoile Sportive du Sahel|ESS]].

He participates with the same club in the [[CAF Champions League]], the [[CAF Confederation Cup]] and the [[CAF Super Cup|CAF Supercup]]. He is thus quarter-finalist of the Champions League in [[2019–20 CAF Champions League|2020]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mortadha Ben Ouanes * CAF Champions League 2019/2020|url=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/index2.php?url=http://www.mondedufoot.fr/fiche_du_joueur/mortadha-ben-ouanes/caf-champions-league-2019-2020/etoile-du-sahel/3/|access-date=8 February 2021|website=archive.wikiwix.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Tunisie - M. Ben Ouannes - Profile avec news, statistiques de carrières et historique - Soccerway|url=https://fr.soccerway.com/players/mortadha-ben-ouanes/328132/|access-date=8 February 2021|website=fr.soccerway.com}}</ref>

On July 2, 2021, at the end of his contract with ESS, he signed a two-year deal with [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa SK]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kasimpasa : Un international tunisien débarque |url=https://www.beinsports.com/fr-fr/football/articles/kasimpasa-un-international-tunisien-debarque |website=bein sports}}</ref>

==International career==
Ben Ouanes played his first match for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]] on 21 September 2019, in a friendly against [[Libya national football team|Libya]]. This match won 1–0 is part of the [[2020 African Nations Championship qualification|qualifiers for the 2020 African Nations Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Strack-Zimmermann|first=Benjamin|title=Mortadha Ben Ouanès|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/75997/Mortadha_Ben_Ouanes.html|access-date=8 February 2021|website=www.national-football-teams.com|language=en}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was included in the list of 27 Tunisian players selected by [[Jalel Kadri]] to compete in the 2023 [[Africa Cup of Nations]], but he withdrew for family reasons.<ref>{{Cite web |title=EN: Seifeddine Jaziri remplace Mortadha Ben Ouanes |url=https://www.mosaiquefm.net/fr/actualites-sport-tunisie/1225337/en-seifeddine-jaziri-remplace-mortadha-ben-ouanes |website=mosaique fm}}</ref>

